### Histograms Revisited
Notes:

```{r Histograms Revisited}
df_yogurt <- read.csv('yogurt.csv')
df_yogurt <- tbl_df(df_yogurt)
str(df_yogurt)

df_yogurt$id <- factor(df_yogurt$id)
ggplot(data = df_yogurt,
       aes(x = price)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 10)
```

***

### Number of Purchases
Notes:

```{r Number of Purchases}
df_yogurt <- transform(df_yogurt, all_purchases = strawberry + blueberry + mixed.berry + pina.colada + plain)

# df_yogurt$all_purchases <- df_yogurt$strawberry + df_yogurt$blueberry + df_yogurt$mixed.berry
df_yogurt <- tbl_df(df_yogurt)
summary(df_yogurt$all_purchases)
```

***

### Prices over Time
Notes:

```{r Prices over Time, fig.width=15, fig.asp=0.3}
ggplot(data = df_yogurt,
       aes(x = time, y = price)) +
  geom_jitter(alpha = 1/4, shape = 21) +
  geom_smooth()
```

